caption.body: Do you or a friend or family member hold material pertaining to the life and legacy of San Francisco Supervisor Harvey B. Milk? SFO Museum invites the public to contribute original photographs, slides, or photographic negatives dating from 1930 to 1980 for consideration as exhibition material in two upcoming two exhibitions scheduled to open in 2019 and 2020 in the San Francisco International Airport’s new Terminal 1: The Harvey B. Milk Terminal.  Harvey B. Milk’s inaugural walk to City Hall from the Castro neighborhood on January 9, 1978. Photographer: Daniel Nicoletta. Submit your photos here: https://www.flysfo.com/museum/programs/harveymilkexhibition
